android.car.hardware

类 CarPropertyValue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.car.hardware.CarPropertyValue<T>
  • 类型参数:
    T - refer to Parcel#writeValue(java.lang.Object) to get a list of all supported types. The class should be visible to framework as default class loader is being used here.

    public final class CarPropertyValue<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Stores a value for a vehicle property ID and area ID combination. Client should use android.car.* types when dealing with property ID, area ID or property value and MUST NOT use android.hardware.automotive.vehicle.* types directly.

    • 构造器详细资料

      • CarPropertyValue

        public CarPropertyValue(int propertyId,
                        int areaId,
                        T value)
        Creates an instance of CarPropertyValue.
        参数:
        propertyId - Property ID, must be one of enums in VehiclePropertyIds.
        areaId - Area ID of Property, must be one of enums in one of the following classes:
        • <VehicleAreaWindow
        • <VehicleAreaDoor
        • <VehicleAreaSeat
        • <VehicleAreaMirror
        • <VehicleAreaWheel
        or 0 for global property.
        value - Value of Property

      • CarPropertyValue

        public CarPropertyValue(int propertyId,
                        int areaId,
                        long timestampNanos,
                        T value)
        Creates an instance of CarPropertyValue. The timestampNanos is the time in nanoseconds at which the event happened. For a given car property, each new CarPropertyValue should be monotonically increasing using the same time base as SystemClock#elapsedRealtimeNanos().
        参数:
        propertyId - Property ID, must be one of enums in VehiclePropertyIds.
        areaId - Area ID of Property, must be one of enums in one of the following classes:
        • <VehicleAreaWindow
        • <VehicleAreaDoor
        • <VehicleAreaSeat
        • <VehicleAreaMirror
        • <VehicleAreaWheel
        or 0 for global property.
        timestampNanos - Elapsed time in nanoseconds since boot
        value - Value of Property

      • getTimestamp

        public long getTimestamp()
        Returns the timestamp in nanoseconds at which the CarPropertyValue happened. For a given car property, each new CarPropertyValue should be monotonically increasing using the same time base as android.os.SystemClock#elapsedRealtimeNanos().

        NOTE: Timestamp should be synchronized with other signals from the platform (e.g. android.location.Location and android.hardware.SensorEvent instances). Ideally, timestamp synchronization error should be below 1 millisecond.
